Scooter Livingston I've mentioned two Gilbert stories before so for the benefit of those new to the group, I will include them in this post.\par
\par
I first saw Gilbert in the flesh at the WNWS Funeral in November '90. Looked like he sounded and I kind of kept my distance. Next time I encountered him was when Neil was at Swap Shop in April '91. Neil had Gilbert go into the audience with a mike. I was sitting next to these two old fart condo commandos who were openly displeased with Neil and let him know. Neil sent Gilbert over to them with the mike and the look of disgust on their faces as Gilbert got near was priceless. I think they were nauseated by Gilbert.\par
\par
I had my personal encounter with him at a Miracle game later that year. I don't remember HOW but somehow he latched on to my now-wife and I. He was following us and he sat with us during the game. He asks me if me and my fiancee want to go "pawty" with him. Yeah right...I told him we had plans and we were bust. Amazingly he didn't persist but I shudder to think what his definition of "pawty" was; I certainly did NOT want to find out and neither did my fiancee.\par
\par
Several months after that, I'm out in San Diego for Grad school. I'm out with some classmates for a few post-night class seminar drinks. I had the local sports staion on. They were carrying a syndicated sports show that was also carried by WQAM as well. "...and now here's Gilbert from Miami..." I let out a scream and hit the steering wheel with my head. I'm asked why. I just tell them to listen to that caller. I then have to explain to them who and WHAT Gilbert is. Even out in San Diego I couldn't escape him.\f1\fs22\lang9\par
